    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "STUDENT_ID  = 2022402195\n",
        "np.random.seed(STUDENT_ID % (2**31))\n",
        "\n",
        "offset_days = STUDENT_ID % 90\n",
        "test_start  = pd.Timestamp(\"2025-07-01\") + pd.Timedelta(days=offset_days)\n",
        "test_end    = test_start + pd.Timedelta(days=27)\n",
        "print(f\"Test window: {test_start.date()} to {test_end.date()}\")"
      ],
      "id": "85304b03",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## About This Assignment\n",
        "\n",
        "In this homework you will apply ARIMA modeling to Turkey's hourly electricity prices (MCP/PTF) and compare it against a regression baseline and a naive benchmark using a rolling 1-day-ahead forecast. This is the same target variable as the class project --- methods you develop here will directly transfer to the forecasting competition starting May 4.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Your personalized test window** is printed above. All your evaluation metrics will be computed over this window. Every student has a different window, so your results will differ from your classmates.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Data Acquisition and Exploration (15 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Load MCP/PTF Data (5 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Download hourly MCP/PTF (Market Clearing Price) data from EPIAS for **2022-01-01 to 2026-03-31**. You can use `eptr2` (Python) or manual download from the EPIAS Transparency Platform, then save as CSV.\n",
        "\n",
        "Split the data using your personalized test window printed above:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Training set:** 2022-01-01 to the day before your `test_start`\n",
        "- **Test set:** Your 4-week window (`test_start` to `test_end`)"
      ],
      "id": "489a4772"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Load merged hourly MCP/PTF data --------------------------------------\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('data/mcp_hourly.csv', parse_dates=['date'])\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={'date': 'Date', 'mcp': 'Price'})\n",
        "df = df.sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Train / test split (hour-based, including last 23 hours of test_end) -\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] <  test_start].copy()\n",
        "test_dt  = df[(df['Date'] >= test_start) &\n",
        "              (df['Date'] <= test_end + pd.Timedelta(hours=23))].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Training observations : {len(train_dt):,}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test observations     : {len(test_dt):,}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Date range            : {df['Date'].min()}  →  {df['Date'].max()}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSummary statistics (Price, TL/MWh):\")\n",
        "print(df['Price'].describe()[['min', 'max', 'mean', '50%']]\n",
        "      .rename({'50%': 'median'}).round(2))"
      ],
      "id": "713735c0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Missing values:** Report count and timestamps of any missing hours. Apply linear interpolation if needed."
      ],
      "id": "f39061d0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# --- Detect missing hours by reindexing to a complete hourly grid ---------\n",
        "full_idx = pd.date_range('2022-01-01 00:00', '2026-03-31 23:00', freq='h')\n",
        "df_indexed   = df.set_index('Date').sort_index()\n",
        "missing_hours = full_idx.difference(df_indexed.index)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Missing hours (count) : {len(missing_hours)}\")\n",
        "if len(missing_hours):\n",
        "    print(f\"Missing timestamps    : {list(missing_hours[:10])}\"\n",
        "          + (\"  …\" if len(missing_hours) > 10 else \"\"))\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Missing timestamps    : (none — data is complete)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Linear interpolation for any gaps (Part 1.1 requirement) -------------\n",
        "df_indexed = df_indexed.reindex(full_idx)\n",
        "df_indexed['Price'] = df_indexed['Price'].interpolate(\n",
        "    method='linear', limit_direction='both')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Refresh df / train_dt / test_dt with the gap-filled series\n",
        "df = df_indexed.reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'Date'})\n",
        "train_dt = df[df['Date'] <  test_start].copy()\n",
        "test_dt  = df[(df['Date'] >= test_start) &\n",
        "              (df['Date'] <= test_end + pd.Timedelta(hours=23))].copy()"
      ],
      "id": "a7cb67e0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Exploratory Visualization (5 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "### Full series plot"
      ],
      "id": "75553239"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 5))\n",
        "ax.plot(df['Date'], df['Price'], color='steelblue', linewidth=0.4)\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.set_title('Hourly MCP / PTF (2022-01-01 — 2026-03-31)', fontsize=13)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Date')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Price (TL/MWh)')\n",
        "ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Annotated events (referenced in the text below) ---------------------\n",
        "# Event 1 — 2022 H2 fuel-price shock + cap revision\n",
