    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**In-sample metrics:**"
      ],
      "id": "116b8c65"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: accuracy-metrics\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def wmape(y, yhat):\n",
        "    # WMAPE: Weighted Mean Absolute Percentage Error\n",
        "    return np.sum(np.abs(y - yhat)) / np.sum(np.abs(y)) * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "def rmse(y, yhat):\n",
        "    # RMSE: Root Mean Squared Error\n",
        "    return np.sqrt(np.mean((y - yhat)**2))\n",
        "\n",
        "def mae(y, yhat):\n",
        "    # MAE: Mean Absolute Error\n",
        "    return np.mean(np.abs(y - yhat))\n",
        "\n",
        "y_true = train_dt['Price']\n",
        "y_pred = model_reg.fittedvalues \n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"In-sample WMAPE: {wmape(y_true, y_pred):.2f}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"In-sample RMSE:  {rmse(y_true, y_pred):.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"In-sample MAE:   {mae(y_true, y_pred):.2f}\")"
      ],
      "id": "accuracy-metrics",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Residual Diagnostics (5 pts)"
      ],
      "id": "21f2a011"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: residual-analysis\n",
        "#| fig-cap: ACF of Regression Residuals\n",
        "\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf\n",
        "from statsmodels.stats.diagnostic import acorr_ljungbox\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# model_reg senin model ismin, ona göre çektik\n",
        "residuals = model_reg.resid\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. ACF Grafiği\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
        "plot_acf(residuals, lags=168, ax=ax)\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"ACF of Regression Residuals\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "residual-analysis",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "lb_test = acorr_ljungbox(residuals, lags=[24, 48, 168])\n",
        "print(lb_test)"
      ],
      "id": "837a4781",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Residual assessment (2-3 sentences):** According to Ljung-Box test results, residuals from the regression are not white noise for lags 24, 48, and 168 (p<0.05). In particular, p-value for lag 168 (p=0.000) proves the absence of fit to the weekly periodicity, indicating that there is no account of 7-day periodicity in the electricity price in the baseline regression model. Furthermore, p-value for lag 24 (p=0.048) proves that although the model takes into account daily periodicity to some degree, it is still insufficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "# ARIMA Modeling (30 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Box-Jenkins on Differenced Prices (10 pts)\n",
        "\n",
        "Using the differencing order you determined in Part 1.3, examine the ACF/PACF to propose candidate ARIMA orders.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
        "## Computation Note\n",
        "ARIMA fitting on long hourly series can be slow. For initial exploration, consider using a recent subset of training data (e.g., last 6 months). Use `stepwise=TRUE, approximation=TRUE` in `auto.arima()` for faster fitting.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "```{r}\n",
        "#| label: arima-identification\n",
        "#| fig-cap: \"ACF and PACF for ARIMA parameter identification\"\n",
        "\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "diff_series = train_dt['Price'].diff(1).diff(24).dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 10))\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_acf(diff_series, lags=168, ax=ax[0])\n",
        "ax[0].set_title(\"ACF of Differenced Series (Identification for q, Q)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_pacf(diff_series, lags=168, ax=ax[1], method='ywm')\n",
        "ax[1].set_title(\"PACF of Differenced Series (Identification for p, P)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "```{r}\n",
        "set.seed(STUDENT_ID)\n",
        "# Candidate 1: auto.arima (non-seasonal)\n",
        "# fit_arima1 <- auto.arima(train_ts, seasonal = FALSE, stepwise = TRUE,\n",
        "#                          approximation = TRUE, trace = TRUE)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "```{r}\n",
        "set.seed(STUDENT_ID)\n",
        "# Candidate 2: manual ARIMA based on ACF/PACF reading\n",
